  "commentary": "With SPX at 6933.92 in PIN regime and sitting between the 6925 (6.2B) and 6950 (16.6B) gamma walls after a -1.6% 5-min drop, dealers are likely covering short hedges and providing buying support as they're long gamma below spot. The massive 16.6B positive gamma wall at 6950 should act as strong resistance, with dealers stepping up selling pressure as price approaches that level. Key levels to watch: 6925 support where dealers ramp buying, 6950 resistance where selling intensifies, and 6900 as secondary support with 8.4B in positive gamma.\n\nBottom line: expect bounce back toward 6950 with strong resistance there, then chop between 6925-6950.",
